<Review ID>9685875
<Product Name>SanDisk Sansa Clip 2 GB MP3 Player (Black)
<Title>Best sound for the buck!
<Date>Sat Feb 16 00:00:00 CST 2008
<Content>I purchased a bunch of these for gifts after Thanksgiving because they were are sale for $35. At this price they are disposable.  I own Sony,Apple,and Creative DAP's.  This is by far the best sounding of all them.  The sound is very rich and smooth compared to the Apple devices I own.  In order to get good sound out of an Apple device I have to rip at 192 kbs. I ripped a CD in WMA at 160 kbs and did a side by side comparison for over 3 hrs on three tracks.  The clip wins hands down.  I also compared the clip to a Sony with the same tracks at 64kbs Atrac.  I still think that Atrac is a superior format but Sony has discontinued support for Atrac and Sonic Stage is a pain to use.  I like the Shuffle because of the smaller size and sturdier clip but the Clip is just as small and has a better battery life.  Compared to a Apple 5.5 G, Nano 3G and Shuffle 2G the Clip has better detail.  It also nice to have FM radio. Which came in handy when I was listening to Classical radio and heard a piece last night on my car radio.  I wanted to hear who the composer was and didn't want to stay in the car to hear the composer.  It was the first time I used the radio on the Clip and found it easy to use and reception was as good as the car radio.  The navigation to find songs was easier than the Shuffle since the Shuffle doesn't have a screen. It fits under a hard hat or clips to a t-shirt for discrete listening when traveling or at work.  You don't know it is there.  I would recommend the clip to anyone that is looking for great sound that is discrete or works in environments that can beat up a DAP.  
<Overall>4

