<Review ID>1097553
<Product Name>SanDisk Sansa Clip 2 GB MP3 Player (Black)
<Title>I love the clip
<Date>Sat Jan 12 00:00:00 CST 2008
<Content>Pros: -The clip (it's removable too, but I don't see a point to removing it) -Couldn't be smaller and still be easy to use -Has more buttons than all players I've used, which makes getting to what you want faster. -The audio quality of this player is near perfect (on normal eq). -Equalizer is perfect also, in case the recording needs it. -I use it during exercise or just put it in my pocket in case I'm stuck in a waiting room (because it is so small and inexpensive).   -Great battery life and battery meter -Uses standard mini USB and not some stupid ipod cable. This also allows you to charge it with your cell phone charger. -FM tuner. I don't use it much as the quality of FM is not good enough for me.  But I feel the tuner is as good as any portable player.  Cons: -The user interface could be better. If you were to compare this against the apple clip (okay, the shuffle) this has a screen!  I prefer the UI of the Apple nano, but the nano is big and expensive, and doesn't have a clip.  The main UI annoyance I have is if the screen is off, the first button you press only lights up the device. You have to press the button again to perform that action. Because the buttons are 'clicky,' and there's button lock, I don't see the need for the first click.  Sansa could easily release new firmware to fix this.  -Not compatible with iTunes purchases.  This is reason not to buy from iTunes.  Consider amazon's mp3 service instead.  
<Overall>5

<Review ID>2919969
<Product Name>SanDisk Sansa Clip 2 GB MP3 Player (Black)
<Title>New technology for a Gramma of seven
<Date>Sat Jan 12 00:00:00 CST 2008
<Content>I asked my daughter for a set of headphones for my portable CD player for Christmas.  I was surprised to say the least when I opened this Sansa Clip 2 GB MP3 Player.  I tried to get her to return it, but she "insisted" that I "just try it".  I'm FAR from being Computer Saavy, but I decided to give it a try.  I plugged it into my laptop and Windows Media Player walked me thru EVERYTHING!  I loaded my whole CD library (40 CD'S) onto this thing and I still have 55 MB left.  The sound is so much BETTER than my CD player, and I'm just using the earbuds that came with it.  This Gramma can now go ANYWHERE and do ANYTHING with her music clipped to her!  I almost hate to admit it, but this time my daughter was right on the money.  I can't THANK HER ENOUGH, for bringing this Gramma into the NEW AGE!  It's ABSOLUTELY WONDERFUL!  If you're on the fence, go for it, don't hesitate!  Ten Stars and two Thumbs Up to SanDisk!  
<Overall>5

<Review ID>2217125
<Product Name>SanDisk Sansa Clip 2 GB MP3 Player (Black)
<Title>Great bang for the buck.
<Date>Mon Jan 14 00:00:00 CST 2008
<Content>I bought this as a gift for a friend, so I don't actually own it. But I did get a chance to use it. For the price, you can't really go wrong. 2GB of storage, FM Tuner and cheaper than a iPod Shuffle. The sound quality is great compared to other budget players I have used in the past. Navigating through the menu was also a breeze. There really wasn't much to it.  My only gripe is that when playback is on random. If you advance tracks, it'll play random as well as if you go back a track. So if you accidentally skip a track you wanted to hear on random, you'll have to go back and search for it. Another thing I had trouble with was connecting to my computer. I've read a few other people having the same problem recognizing the device in Windows. Since its not my player, I wasn't going to lose sleep over it. My friend, however, didn't have any problems connecting.  
