<Review ID>7869646
<Product Name>SanDisk Sansa Clip 2 GB MP3 Player (Black)
<Title>Fantastic little player.
<Date>Sun Jan 20 00:00:00 CST 2008
<Content>I bought this to replace my 2nd gen iPod Shuffle.  It's so nice having twice the space (at half the cost) and also having the capability of playing playlists or playing by genre/artist/album.  The user interface on the Clip is very intuitive and well designed.  The screen is bright and easy to see in most any environment.  The Clip is extremely light weight and small enough to clip anywhere you desire.  Also, the sound quality is excellent for a player as small and inexpensive as the Clip.  It is a night and day difference with the iPod Shuffle.  And, the headphones included are nicer than I expected.  The player works perfectly in Ubuntu.  Upon plugging it in, it automatically mounts and nautilus opens allowing me to drag and drop music directly onto the device.  Yay for the linux love!  I am only disappointed that it doesn't have a charging dock and it is plastic rather than metal (this does, however, make it weigh less).  It still seems well built and the buttons give good feedback.  We'll see how it holds up over time.  Otherwise, I am highly satisfied and would definitely recommend this player.  I have used several mp3 players over the years (Apple, iAudio, etc) and this one takes the cake.  Buy it.  You won't be disappointed.  
<Overall>5

<Review ID>9465868
<Product Name>SanDisk Sansa Clip 2 GB MP3 Player (Black)
<Title>100% Satisfied
<Date>Mon Jan 21 00:00:00 CST 2008
<Content>This is my first purchase of an mp3 player.  I'm a gigging musician who has never purchased anything less than high-end audio components for my home.  My ears are spoiled and so are my family's, so I haven't been too quick to jump on the mp3 bandwagon.  I bought this for my 10 year old son for Christmas.  If you simply want to listen to music, this is a GREAT product.  The sound quality of this little unit is pretty darn good right out of the box.  I may upgrade to another set of ear-plug style headphones to see how much of a difference it will make, but the ones that came with it sound pretty good.  The EQ presets are a nice feature, but the only one I would ever use is the "Jazz" preset - it cuts better at full range than the others for any style of music.  My son was able to figure out how to operate it after a few quick pointers, and I'm sure that he knows it better than me now.  The only drawback, of course, is the memory size.  2 GB fills up pretty quick.  But I knew that going in.  It is what it is - a great sounding entry unit!  I'll probably be getting a couple more for my other 2 sons.  
<Overall>4

<Review ID>1356635
<Product Name>SanDisk Sansa Clip 2 GB MP3 Player (Black)
<Title>Tiny size. Handy clip. Great sound. Nice features. Get one.
<Date>Wed Jan 23 00:00:00 CST 2008
<Content>A fashionable salesgirl at Benetton asked me about my cute little MP3 player. She said her iPod had broken, and she wasn't ready to pay $200 to replace it.  She asked me if the Sansa works with Macintosh.  I said "of course."  I let her play with the Sansa for a bit; and within minutes, she HAD to go straight out to buy one after work.    Why did she fall in love with my Sansa Clip, and not me?  Tiny, cute, fun and easy interface. Check.  Works with her Macintosh and her friend's PC. Check.  Plenty of space for her favorite songs. Check.  15-hour battery life for a girl on-the-go. Check.  Clips discretely to her cute outfits. Check.  Excellent sound quality with nice earphones. Check.  FM Radio that can record songs off-the-air. Check.  She can tape boring lectures with the microphone. Check.  Costs 1/2 of what a replacement iPod would cost?  Check.  Plays her favorite videos? No, sorry.   Syncs with iTunes?  Nope.  But it works great with Windows Media Player and VLC or other non-iTunes players on the Macintosh.  This is just what everybody needs:  A tiny, great-sounding, light, music player that weighs nothing, holds 500+ songs and clips to any clothing. I'm selling my iPod.                
<Overall>5

