<Content>I'm an iPod guy, but bought this to use with Overdrive audio books from the library. It sounds great and works without a ton of extraneous software. The one thing I do wish the unit had was the ability to bookmark, but Sandisk seems to update firmware frequently so there is always hope. The build quality is OK but the plastic is a little creaky. It seems to be a bit fragile and perhaps not up to the build quality of the iPod Nano or Shuffle. Still, I'm glad I bought this - its a great little player and I recommend it.  
