<Review ID>2822073
<Product Name>SanDisk Sansa Clip 2 GB MP3 Player (Black)
<Title>nicely designed, but I got a dud battery
<Date>Sun Jan 27 00:00:00 CST 2008
<Content>I recently read up on small flash-memory players, and bought the Sansa Clip, which is well-reviewed and reputed to have very good sound quality for a tiny player. I found it impressively small yet easy to operate. The built-in clip is convenient, and the player is not so small that it's easy to lose. The only downside with the physical design is the volume buttons on the right side - it's a little loose and can rattle (other reviewers have noted this too) though that doesn't really pose any problem for the player. Also, the headphone jack is right by the volume control and L-jack headphones can make getting at the volume button a pain. The little screen really makes the player better and menus are easy to navigate. I wish the screen had one more line on it, but not a big deal.  One problem is that the player can't read ID3v2.4 tags, so in the case of longer song or album names, the player will only show the ID3v1 tags which are limited to 30 characters. So I retagged my mp3's for ID3v2.3 which the Sansa will read.  While most people have had good experiences with the Sansa Clip, my battery is a dud and stopped retaining charge within a week of my getting the unit. I can charge it up (which takes 2.5-3 hours, btw) and it shows full charge, but loses charge rapidly over time (though will play fine until time, not usage, has drained the battery). So I'm returning my unit. But this seems to be the exception, and I didn't downgrade the Clip much for this.  
<Overall>4

