<Review ID>5357462
<Product Name>SanDisk Sansa Clip 2 GB MP3 Player (Black)
<Title>Great little player with features to spare
<Date>Sat Feb 09 00:00:00 CST 2008
<Content>SanDisk's Sansa Clip is an amazing little device.  I've owned iPods before, and I'm pretty tech savvy. (a computer engineering student in college)  The sound quality is great for such a portable device.  The battery life could be better but honestly, on a player this tiny, I can't see a reason why you'd need such a long battery life--with only 2GB space it's not designed to be brought on long trips or things like that.  Simply enough, you can just drag and drop any music you want on the MP3 player.  Anyway, my point is, think of an iPod shuffle.  Now give yourself an FM radio, voice controls, recording controls, a lower overall price, a higher capacity, and probably most importantly, the ability to CHOOSE a song.  I also love that it uses a standard USB mini port, because I have other cords that are compatible.  The only two problems I have are that I wish there was a power cord for a wall outlet, and it's not possible to copy music from my MP3 player to my hard drive.  But it's nothing worth docking it a star, so I'm going to fully recommend this device as the best MP3 player I've used.  Oh, also, I tried this player using Ubuntu 7.10 (Gutsy Gibbon) and it does in fact work properly.  I was able to drag and drop music to the player.  The only problem is that I got copies of artists when I did this.  Ubuntu didn't see the folders that I added from windows properly, so I wound up with 2 separate folders for any artists I added with both drives.  (i.e. I added one song by Weezer using Windows, and another song by Weezer in Ubuntu, and the player now shows them as two separate artists, both named "Weezer", but each containing a different song)  So, it will most likely work in Ubuntu, but only really if you add songs using one OS only.  Again, a better positive than negative.  
<Overall>5

<Review ID>7073208
<Product Name>SanDisk Sansa Clip 2 GB MP3 Player (Black)
<Title>Much better player than the Zen Stone plus
<Date>Fri Nov 23 00:00:00 CST 2007
<Content>The Sansa clip is an outstanding player in the compact, on the go field of MP3 players. I've had or have used a few other players in this range and bought the Zen Stone Plus a few months back. The Sansa clip is better than the Stone Plus in just about every way possible. The most notable aspects where the Sansa clip is superior is the battery life (about 2x that of the Stone Plus) and ease of use. The LCD display is also much nicer on the Sansa clip. And of course the Sansa clip has....the clip, while the Stone doesn't, so that's an extra expense.  Anybody looking for a compact player can't go wrong with the Sansa clip. The only down-side I found is that my 5 year old PC with USB 1.1 can't charge the Sansa clip nor will it recognize the clip in MTP mode, while the Stone Plus doesn't have this issue. If you have a newer PC with USB 2.0 it's not an issue. My PC will recognize the Sansa clip in MSC mode, however.  
<Overall>5

